{"DAD":[{"def":"Father; -- a word sometimes used by children.","pos":""}],"DADDLE":[{"def":"To toddle; to walk unsteadily, like a child or an old man; hence, to do anything slowly or feebly.","pos":""}],"DADDOCK":[{"def":"The rotten body of a tree.","pos":""}],"DADDY":[{"def":"Diminutive of Dad.","pos":""}],"DADDY LONGLEGS":[{"def":"An arachnidan of the genus Phalangium, and allied genera, having a small body and four pairs of long legs; -- called also harvestman, carter, and grandfather longlegs.","pos":""},{"def":"A name applied to many species of dipterous insects of the genus Tipula, and allied genera, with slender bodies, and very long, slender legs; the crane fly; -- called also father longlegs.","pos":""}],"DADE":[{"def":"To hold up by leading strings or by the hand, as a child while he toddles.","pos":""}],"DADO":[{"def":"Cunningly or ingeniously formed or working; skillful; artistic; ingenious.","pos":""},{"def":"Crafty; deceitful.","pos":""}]}